Q2. Write a Python program that accepts text file name and a string. If file exist, then appends string to its content and display the contents of the file otherwise gives appropriate message. 

filename = input("Enter file name: ")
text = input("Enter text to append: ")
try:
        with open(filename, "a") as f:
        f.write(text + "\n")
    with open(filename, "r") as f:
        print("\nUpdated File Content:\n")
        print(f.read())
except FileNotFoundError:
    print("File does not exist.")
except Exception as e:
    print("Error:", e)
